Subject: French & Morphology: Researcher, Universitaet Konstanz, Germany 
 

University or Organization: Universitaet Konstanz 
Department: Linguistics
Job Rank: Researcher  
Specialty Areas: Historical Linguistics; Morphology; French Language
Required Language(s): French (fra)


Description:

Applications are invited for a half-time research position for three years (not
 renewable) in a research project on 'Morphological variation and change',
funded by the Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (German Research Foundation) as
part of the Sonderforschungsbereich 471 'Variation and evolution in the
lexicon'. The successful applicant is expected to undertake research toward
their PhD in linguistics.

Project description: 
The project investigates phenomena of variation and change at the
morphology-phonology interface in Romance, especially French and Italian.
The focus is on both, data retrieval and linguistic theory.

More information about the project may be obtained at:
http://www.uni-konstanz.de/tt/forschdb/Fodb000.html

Requirements:
Applicants should have an M.A. degree (or equivalent) in linguistics.
They should be prepared to read Old or Middle French texts and have
experience in morphological or phonological analysis.

Applicants should send a cover letter, a full CV and a sample publication
or paper to: 

Christoph Schwarze
christoph.schwarze@uni-konstanz.de
Fachbereich Sprachwissenschaft
Postfach D 176
Universitaet Konstanz
D-78457 Konstanz
Germany

Applications will be considered until <deadline>December 20th, 2005</deadline> (or beyond if the
positions have not been filled by then). The positions are available as of
January 1, though a later start date can also be negotiated. The University
of Konstanz is an equal opportunity employer and tries to increase the 
number of women in research and teaching. The University encourages
disabled persons, who will be given preference if appropriately 
qualified, to apply (Contact +49-7531-883725).


