Subject: Mres in Speech, Language and Cognition at Ucl: MA / MSc Student, UCL, United Kingdom 

	
-------------------------Message 1 ---------------------------------- 
Date: Thu, 08 Dec 2005 16:46:17
From: Stefanie Anyadi < stefanie@ling.ucl.ac.uk >
Subject: Mres in Speech, Language and Cognition at Ucl: MA / MSc Student, UCL, United Kingdom 
 

University or Organization: UCL
Job Rank: MA / MSc  
Specialty Areas: Cognitive Science; Discipline of Linguistics; Language
Acquisition; Neurolinguistics; Psycholinguistics 


Centre for Human Communication Award for Students in the MRes in Speech,
Language and Cognition at UCL

One award of £500 is available for the MRes in Speech, Language and Cognition
administered by the UCL Department of Phonetics and Linguistics on behalf of the
Centre for Human Communication.

The interdisciplinary MRes in Speech, Language and Cognition is aimed at
applicants whose interest in language spans more than one discipline. Building
on a first degree in linguistics, speech sciences, psychology, cognitive
science, or a cognate discipline, students plan their own course of study (with
the guidance of an advisor), selecting from a range of courses in several
different UCL departments. The degree is a stand-alone 12-month Masters, but is
also excellent preparation for PhD research in a language-related field of study.

Application Procedure: 
Applicants should write indicating their intention to compete for the bursary to
Stefanie Anyadi at the address below.


Mailing Address for Applications:

Ms Stefanie Anyadi
Department of Phonetics and Linguistics
University College London
Gower Street
London WC1E 6BT
United Kingdom

Applications are due by <deadline>15-May-2006</deadline>

Contact Information:

Stefanie Anyadi
Email: s.anyadi@ling.ucl.ac.uk
Tel: + 44 20 7679 7172 / 7174
Fax: +44 (0) 20 7383 4108





